Add start-lock script to serialize flow-start because concurrent starts fight over main.

tl;dr

Multiple simultaneous flow-start sessions can run CI fixes and dependency
updates on main at the same time, causing conflicts. A file lock at
.flow-states/start.lock ensures only one start runs at a time. PID-based
stale detection with a 30-minute timeout handles crashed sessions.

- lib/start-lock.py: New script with acquire/release/check subcommands, PID stale detection via os.getppid() and os.kill(pid, 0), 30-min timeout fallback, corrupted/empty lock handling
- tests/test_start_lock.py: 20 tests covering acquire (free, locked, stale PID, timeout, corrupted, empty, missing keys, PermissionError), release (normal, idempotent), check (free, locked, dead PID), and CLI integration — Task 1 of 5
